args:
As Ilia and her companions scour the memories
of the Sacred Tree for a means to counter the
Progenitor, they learn the Five Greatwyrms had
once succeeded in resealing the restored
Progenitor. This discovery lights a new fire of
hope within them all.
Sacred Tree: Lower Strata\nBough of Recollection
Okay, that's weird. It's supposed to be\nhere, but...
Would you please tell me why we have\nreturned to the Sacred Tree, Ilia?
Do you believe we might discover some\nmeans here by which we can oppose\nthe Progenitor?
Maybe, maybe not. That's why we're\nhere to poke around.
There is no need to speak in such riddles.\nFor all we know, the Progenitor could be\nreturned even as we speak.
So listen. If my little hunch is correct,\nthe Progenitor has already been brought\nback into this world at least once.
And what proof do you have for this\nmad claim?
The proof is me and Zethia.
Yeah, and I'm not a hundred percent\ncertain either, which is why I wanted to\ncome here and make sure.
The Sacred Tree has existed as far back\nas when the Progenitor and Origin were\nstill kicking around.
And all of its memories from that time\nshould still be inside it.
If the Progenitor has been restored at\nsome point in the past, it will remember.
Then ought we not simply ask the will of\nthe tree if it remembers such?
That would save a whole lot of effort—\nbut unfortunately, the tree has too many\nmemories for the single will to hold.
So the memories are separated from\nthe will and stored in the trunk and roots,\nwhich is what we need to look for.
Since it's a pretty old memory, I assume\nit'll be in the roots. There should be a\nhollow in the tree that leads there...
Ah, there we are. Right, team! In we go!
So the Sacred Tree's memories\nare held in this place?
Better to say that they're the world's\nmemories, since the Sacred Tree is\nconnected to mana founts everywhere.
Now we just have to search for a memory\nof a time when the Progenitor appeared.
And how do we do that, exactly?
Upon this ground shall you\nbe sealed away once more!
A memory of the Sacred Tree from\nroughly three hundred years ago.
That appeared to be from the moment\nwhere Alberius was fighting Morsayati.
Yeah, we need to go way older than that.\nLet's keep digging.
Oh geez, it's just a memory. Man,\nthat startled me...
That was Meene, which means this is a\nmemory from a thousand years ago.
Really could have done without that\nbeing shoved back into my face.
No time for whining. Let's keep going.\n...Although I REALLY did a number on\npoor Meene, huh?
I'm quite certain she would understand.
We are so deep now. Just how far back\ndo these memories go?
We've gone past the memories of the\nancient Qilin civilization, so this must\nbe tens of thousands of years back.
I would remind you that we have no proof\nthat the Progenitor ever returned to this\nworld in the past.
This may have all been a colossal\nwaste of time.
That can't be... I was sure...\nOkay, this is really weird.
Everyone, stop! I just heard a voice saying\n＂Progenitor＂!
Fie, but this is black mana! Urgh...\nThough it be but a memory, it is still\nincredibly oppressive!
It's the Progenitor! The Progenitor lies\nbeyond this black mana!
This is it! This is a memory of a time\nwhen the Progenitor was returned!
For the sake of this world...\npossibility must be protected...
So Elysium stood against the Progenitor...

This is the end of everything...
You seek to destroy this world and
create a new one in its place...?
We must put a stop to this!
A pact is a pact...\nIf that is your will, I shall obey...\nReduce me to mana...
But how is that possible...\nYou have some nerve...\nYou have trifled with the wrong dragon!
Valor does not make a victor...\nSuch things are not pleasant for dragons...

This warped world...
This place of determination and despair...
Let it now banish this threat...
I will have my pride returned!
It's an incredibly old memory by the looks\nof it, and there were a lot of bits that were\nfragmentary and unclear...
But I think it was Elysium and the other\ndragons defeating the Progenitor.
That didn't look like ＂defeating＂ him.\nIt appeared more like they stopped his\nrevival, or perhaps resealed him.
Even so, that's still valuable information\nfor us right now.
With the combined power of the dragons,\nthe Progenitor can be opposed!
So were those dragons just now...?
The Five Greatwyrms? I suspect so,\nalthough they looked different.

Eminent dragons like the Five are reborn
in new forms after they die. The way they
appear now is likely the result of their
having been reborn several times.
Then if we combine the powers of the\nFive Greatwyrms, we should be able to\noppose the Progenitor?
Sadly, I fear the current Five Greatwyrms\nlack the power to face our foe.
When they're reborn, they end up losing\ntheir memories. Midgardsormr seems to\nnot even recognize me.
And if their memories are lost, it stands\nto reason some power would be as well.
In other words, the Five Greatwyrms can't\nhelp and this was all a waste of time.
Easy on the depressing assumptions\nthere, pal.
The Five Greatwyrms are still the Five\nGreatwyrms. If they've lost their power,\nthey'll just have to get it back.
Let's head back to Grams, everybody.\nWe've finally got some good news!
